{"data":{"actions":[{"callId":"chatcmpl-tool-b537f6abbf6726ce","input":{"filename":"action_report.md","title":"Test Failure Debugger Prioritized Action Report","markdown":"# Test Failure Debugger – Prioritized Action Report (≤500 words)\n\n**Evidence**\n- Dossier loaded (agent ID: 15-test-failure-debugger).\n- Operational records analyzed (3 items, risk/opportunity scores).\n\n## 1. Immediate High‑Impact Action – Record **15‑A**\n- **Status:** urgent\n- **Impact:** 46,755 (highest)\n- **Risk Score:** 6 / Opportunity 6.7\n- **Summary:** Core functionality – reading failing logs, identifying cause, proposing a fix – is pending.\n\n**Proposed Steps**\n1. **Run end‑to‑end sanity test**: `npm run test -- --grep \"Test failure debugger\"` (or the project‑specific test command) to reproduce the failure and capture logs.\n2. **Collect logs** from the latest run (typically under `logs/` or CI artifact) and feed them to the agent for root‑cause analysis.\n3. **Validate fix** by re‑executing the same test suite after applying the proposed code change; success is confirmed when the test exits with status 0 and no new failures appear.\n\n**Assumptions**\n- The test suite is accessible locally and can be run without external dependencies.\n- Log files are stored in a conventional location.\n\n## 2. Blocked Follow‑Up – Record **15‑C**\n- **Status:** blocked (requires cross‑functional coordination)\n- **Impact:** 21,165\n- **Risk Score:** 8 / Opportunity 2.1\n\n**Action to Unblock**\n- Identify the dependent team/component (e.g., the CI pipeline or a shared library) via the ticketing system.\n- Schedule a brief sync (≤30 min) to obtain required access or clarification.\n- Document the dependency in the agent’s knowledge base to avoid future blocks.\n\n**Assumptions**\n- The blocker is a non‑technical policy or access issue rather than a code defect.\n\n## 3. Routine Review – Record **15‑B**\n- **Status:** in_review\n- **Impact:** 10,695\n- **Risk Score:** 1 / Opportunity 1.1\n\n**Suggested Action**\n- Perform a lightweight code review of the agent’s log‑parsing module to ensure it follows current schema versions.\n- No immediate validation needed; treat as maintenance.\n\n## Prioritization Summary\n| Rank | Record | Impact | Risk | Status | Immediate Next Step |\n|------|--------|--------|------|--------|----------------------|\n| 1 | 15‑A | 46,755 | 6 | urgent | Run test, collect logs, propose fix, validate with re‑run |\n| 2 | 15‑C | 21,165 | 8 | blocked | Resolve external dependency via coordination |\n| 3 | 15‑B | 10,695 | 1 | in_review | Conduct code review / minor refactor |\n\n## Next Actions (Owner: Engineering)\n1. Execute the validation command for **15‑A** and capture results.\n2. Reach out to the blocking team for **15‑C** and log progress.\n3. Schedule a 1‑hour review window for **15‑B** within the next sprint.\n\n*All recommendations are based on the current operational record analysis. Adjustments may be required as new evidence emerges.*\n"},"kind":"tool-call","toolName":"write_report"}],"sequence":0,"stepIndex":3,"turnId":"turn_0"},"type":"actions.requested","meta":{"at":"2026-06-18T15:11:41.132Z"}}
